title: Noisy Neighbors
description: Nanny warns the Babies not to make so much noise, because their next door neighbor is a police officer who works a night shift and sleeps during the day.

title: Who's Afraid of the Big, Bad Dark?
description: When Bunsen and Beaker come over to spend the night. The Babies must help Beaker overcome his fear of the dark.

title: Dental Hyjinks
description: Fozzie has a toothache and all the babies imagine what will happen to him at the dentist's office.

title: Scooter's Hidden Talent
description: Scooter's upset that everybody else was able to put together an exercise bike for Nanny's birthday except him; so Kermit and the others try to help Scooter figure out what he's good at.

title: The Case of the Missing Chicken
description: Everybody becomes a suspect in Gonzo's book when his stuffed chicken Camilla disappears and he suspects 'fowl play'.

title: Eight Take-Away One Equals Panic
description: The babies overhear Nanny having a conversation on the telephone and are led to believe that she's going to get rid of one of them.

title: What Do You Want to Be When You Grow Up?
description: While the Babies, were discussing what they wanted to be, when they grown up but, Kermit was having problems deciding. Finally, the Babies decided, to give Kermit, some advice for future careers.

title: Close Encounters of the Frog Kind
Gonzo's Video Show
description: Nanny has rented a video camera recorder and allows the babies to play with it unattended for an hour. Gonzo takes charge behind the camera and the gang decides to remake

title: Fun Park Fantasies
description: The babies are too excited to sleep because Nanny's taking them to the fun park the next day, and they imagine what adventures lie ahead for them at the park.

title: From a Galaxy Far, Far Away
description: While the babies are playing aliens from another planet, a strange creature breaks into the nursery and they become convinced it's a baby alien and try to hide it from the man looking for it.

title: Once Upon an Egg Timer
description: When Rowlf loses his voice in an accident, Nanny suggests the Babies take turns telling a story with a egg timer until it comes back.

title: Piggy's Hyper-Activity Book
description: On a rainy day, the babies play special games, in the activity book to overcome their boredom.

title: Out-of-This-World-History
description: The babies learn about American History involving George Washington and the Revolution of 1776 through an old book, while Gonzo looks for his own kind of history (outer space science fiction).

title: Snow White and the Seven Muppets
The Great Muppet Cartoon Show
description: The Babies make their own animated films.

title: The Muppet Museum of Art
description: When Nanny cancels a trip to the art museum after Skeeter sprains her ankle, the babies start their own museum in the nursery.

title: When You Wish Upon a Muppet
Pigerella
description: Piggy imagines she is Cinderella.

title: The Best Friend I Never Had
Muppets in Toyland
description: The other babies become jealous when Scooter gets a brand new remote control robot; but they use their imaginations and some of Nanny's old toys to have some fun of their own.

title: The Muppet Broadcasting Company
description: During a power outage, Nanny gives the Babies some tapes of old-time radio shows to listen to.

title: Fozzie's Family Tree
description: The Babies explore a "Family Tree" and learn about their ancestors.

title: The Daily Muppet
description: When Nanny's newspaper is soaked from sitting out in the rain, The Babies decide to make their own newspaper for her.

title: Scooter's Uncommon Cold
description: When Scooter gets a cold, the Babies shrink themselves to help him fight his illness.

roles.char: Captain of the Pittsburgh Pirates the Green Pirette
Captain Crochette Hook the Pink Pirette

title: Muppet Goose
description: Nanny reads the Babies nursery rhymes.

title: Bad Luck Bear
description: Fozzie accidentally cracks the bathroom mirror and the others are convinced he's stuck with seven years bad luck.

title: Of Mice and Muppets
description: The babies are pet-sitting for Officer Caruthers's pet mouse, but panic ensues when they find the cage door open and the mouse gone.

title: Back to the Nursery
description: When one of Nanny's favorite photographs, a picture of her working as a carhop in the 1950s gets ruined, the Babies travel back in time to replace it.

title: Muppetland
description: Kermit gets invited to a birthday party at the amusement park, but it's two weeks away so the babies decide to make their own fun parks in the meantime.

title: The Incredible Shrinking Weirdo
description: When the Muppets get their sport jerseys back from the laundry, Gonzo's is too large and he worries he's shrinking, while Fozzie's is too tight and he fears he'll become a giant.

title: Where No Muppet Has Gone Before
Journey to the Center of the Nursery
description: When Fozzie loses his skate key in an air vent during an earthquake, the babies journey below the Earth to look for it.

title: This Little Piggy Went to Hollywood
description: Piggy daydreams about being Hollywood star.

title: My Muppet Valentine
description: On Valentine's Day, Nanny gives the babies special cookies, but Rowlf doesn't get one and becomes depressed.

title: Invasion of the Muppet Snackers
description: Kermit and his friends stumble upon Nanny making something slimy and disgusting and worry it's a new food for them to eat.

title: Twinkle Toe Muppets
description: The Babies argue over what kind of dancing is better.

title: Weirdo for the Prosecution
description: The cookie jar in the kitchen is broken and Gonzo quickly becomes the prime suspect; so Scooter decides they should give him a fair trial to determine his innocence or guilt.

title: Muppet Island
description: After the Babies accidentally spill jelly all over the hallway. Nanny tells them they have to stay in the nursery, where they imagine that they are on a deserted island.

title: The Frog Who Knew Too Much
description: Kermit stumbles upon Nanny preparing a surprise for them for the next morning and promises not to tell anyone; but the other babies spend the night trying to get Kermit to confess to what he saw.

title: The House That Muppets Built
description: When the Babies destroy Piggy's doll house, while playing football. They help her build a new one.

title: Masquerading Muppets
description: The babies get invited to a costume party and Nanny gives them a box of old costumes for them to pick from; Gonzo goes through several and has trouble deciding which one to be.

title: Nanny's Day Off
description: The babies declare it Nanny's Day and give her the day off while they take over the cooking and cleaning, and the most important job of finishing her big surprise.

title: The Pig Who Would Be Queen
Is There a Muppet in the House?
description: Rowlf disappears during nap time on a stormy day and everybody thinks he's been kidnapped by ghosts.

title: Slipping Beauty
description: Piggy gets chicken pox, the other babies tell her a story to cheer her up.

title: He's a Wonderful Frog
description: Kermit is scheduled to leave to visit his family in the swamp, the Babies wonder what they would do without him.

title: Elm Street Babies
description: When the Babies can't sleep, they tell each other about their dreams.

title: Plan 8 from Outer Space
description: When the Babies see a news bulletin on TV about how Prince Charles and Princess Diana cannot find a nanny for their two sons, they soon think all the nannies on Earth, including theirs, have been abducted by aliens.

title: The Air Conditioner at the End of the Galaxy
This Old Nursery
description: The babies find a time capsule and learn about the people who used to live their house.

title: And Now a Word from Our Muppets
description: The Babies make advertisements to help Nanny with her garage sale.

title: Six to Eight Weeks
description: The babies await the arrival a playhouse they ordered.

title: Comic Capers
description: The babies read the Sunday comics and decide to make their own.

title: Skeeter and the Wolf
description: The babies learn about "Peter and the Wolf".

title: The New Adventures of Kermo Polo
description: Nanny tells the Babies about Marco Polo and other famous explorers of his era.

title: Goosetown Babies
description: Gonzo and Animal journey to "Goosetown", where all the nursery rhymes live to repair, their old "Mother Goose" book.

title: It's Only Pretendo
description: The Babies play video games.

title: Quoth the Weirdo
description: The Babies recite their favorite poems.

title: Operators Are Standing By
description: When Animal answers phone and than hangs up, due to the fact he is still too young to talk good enough to understand, the Babies wonder who was trying to call them

title: Babes in Troyland
description: The Babies learn about Greek mythology.

title: A Punch Line to the Tummy
Muppet Babies: The Next Generation
description: The Babies parody "Star Wars", "The Jetsons", and "Star Trek".

title: Buckskin Babies
description: The Babies learn about early American folk heroes.

title: Sing a Song of Superheroes
description: When Nanny announces the water has been shut off in the neighborhood, the babies pretend to be superheroes such as Batman, The Wonder Twins, and The Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles to get it back!

title: Gonzee's Playhouse Channel
description: The Babies pretend they have their own TV channel and do spoofs of "Pee-Wee's Playhouse", "Sesame Street", "Beetlejuice", and other popular kids shows.

title: Whose Tale Is It, Anyway?
description: When Bean invites his friend, Janice over, Piggy is jealous about her ability to read.

title: In Search of the Bronzed Beetle
Get Me to the Perch on Time
Bearly Alone Babies
description: The babies overhear the news mention a ski-mask burglar called "Mad Dog Marvin" has escaped from jail and they think he's heading their way; as Nanny tries to get the house locked up before a storm hits.

title: Nice to Have Gnome You
description: Piggy's Alice in Wonderland book is due back at the library but she can't find it; Gonzo thinks goblins took it and the muppets try to make a new one before Nanny comes for it.

title: Eight Flags Over the Nursery
description: The Babies create their own theme park, after seeing an ad on TV for a theme park, expected to open nearly 5 years in the future.
